[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     66[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `_detect_coordination_scope_violation` looks at the **response text** (not the user message) and the response contains none of the dose-titration trigger phrases (`"increase your dose"`, `"go up to"`, etc.).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     67[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `_contains_deference` matches `"i'm not making the"` in the response, so `_suggests_clinical_judgment` short-circuits the conservative-bias check.
